  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a HarfBuzz color value with BGRA byte ordering.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`HBColor` wraps a HarfBuzz `hb_color_t` value, which stores color channels in BGRA order
(`0xBBGGRRAA` — blue in the high byte, alpha in the low byte). This differs from
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses ARGB order (`0xAARRGGBB`).

Use the named properties (<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>,
<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha>) rather than
manipulating the raw <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Value> directly, to avoid byte-order errors.

`HBColor` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from individual components
var color = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 128, blue: 0, alpha: 255);
Console.WriteLine($"R={color.Red} G={color.Green} B={color.Blue} A={color.Alpha}");

// Convert from SKColor
using var face = new Face(blob, 0);
var paletteColors = face.GetPaletteColors(0);
SKColor skColor = paletteColors[0].ToSKColor();
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
